WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.590 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:13.590 --> 00:00:16.210 align:middle line:84%
>> I think for some
of us to wake up,

00:00:16.210 --> 00:00:17.590 align:middle line:90%
we need a wake-up call.

00:00:17.590 --> 00:00:19.650 align:middle line:90%
And in 1986, I got the call.

00:00:19.650 --> 00:00:23.700 align:middle line:84%
I was in a triathlon in
Palm Springs, California.

00:00:23.700 --> 00:00:26.680 align:middle line:84%
And I was on the biking
portion of the race.

00:00:26.680 --> 00:00:27.870 align:middle line:90%
And I was making a turn.

00:00:27.870 --> 00:00:30.970 align:middle line:84%
And there was a police
officer on the corner.

00:00:30.970 --> 00:00:33.360 align:middle line:84%
And he was pointing to
me to make the turn.

00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:36.120 align:middle line:84%
But he had his back to
the oncoming traffic.

00:00:36.120 --> 00:00:38.350 align:middle line:84%
So I was passing two
cyclists on the corner.

00:00:38.350 --> 00:00:41.490 align:middle line:84%
And when I made the turn,
a four-wheel drive vehicle

00:00:41.490 --> 00:00:45.720 align:middle line:84%
going pretty fast catapulted
me out of my bike.

00:00:45.720 --> 00:00:50.290 align:middle line:84%
When I landed, I broke
six vertebrae in my spine.

00:00:50.290 --> 00:00:52.920 align:middle line:84%
And when you land in
a vertical position,

00:00:52.920 --> 00:00:56.790 align:middle line:84%
the compressive force takes
the columns of the vertebrae

00:00:56.790 --> 00:00:57.790 align:middle line:90%
and flattens them.

00:00:57.790 --> 00:01:00.720 align:middle line:84%
So I had compressed
six vertebrae.

00:01:00.720 --> 00:01:02.430 align:middle line:84%
But when you compress
those vertebrae,

00:01:02.430 --> 00:01:05.670 align:middle line:84%
the volume of that mass
has to go somewhere.

00:01:05.670 --> 00:01:08.520 align:middle line:84%
And it went back
against my spinal cord.

00:01:08.520 --> 00:01:11.370 align:middle line:84%
When my body landed, it
kind of whipped forward.

00:01:11.370 --> 00:01:16.980 align:middle line:84%
And the top vertebrae out
of the six that were broken

00:01:16.980 --> 00:01:19.140 align:middle line:90%
was more than 60% collapsed.

00:01:19.140 --> 00:01:21.600 align:middle line:84%
And the arch that the
spinal cord passed through

00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:23.940 align:middle line:90%
had broken like a pretzel.

00:01:23.940 --> 00:01:26.400 align:middle line:84%
So I had multiple
compression fractures.

00:01:26.400 --> 00:01:28.860 align:middle line:84%
I had bone fragments
on a spinal cord.

00:01:28.860 --> 00:01:31.860 align:middle line:84%
And I had the neural arch of
the 8th thoracic vertebrae

00:01:31.860 --> 00:01:33.750 align:middle line:90%
compressing the cord.

00:01:33.750 --> 00:01:36.300 align:middle line:84%
And I was in a little
bit of trouble.

00:01:36.300 --> 00:01:38.835 align:middle line:84%
And I had four
opinions from four

00:01:38.835 --> 00:01:41.160 align:middle line:84%
of the leading surgeons
in Southern California.

00:01:41.160 --> 00:01:45.030 align:middle line:84%
And a typical surgery
for that type of injury

00:01:45.030 --> 00:01:47.130 align:middle line:84%
is called the
Harrington rod surgery.

00:01:47.130 --> 00:01:49.230 align:middle line:84%
And they do a
complete laminectomy

00:01:49.230 --> 00:01:51.340 align:middle line:84%
of the back parts
of your vertebrae.

00:01:51.340 --> 00:01:53.970 align:middle line:84%
And they cut them
all, back parts, off.

00:01:53.970 --> 00:01:56.340 align:middle line:84%
And then they screw in these
long stainless steel rods.

00:01:56.340 --> 00:01:59.250 align:middle line:84%
And in my case, it was
from the base of my neck

00:01:59.250 --> 00:02:00.280 align:middle line:90%
to the base of my spine.

00:02:00.280 --> 00:02:03.540 align:middle line:84%
They're we're going to
fuse my entire spine to try

00:02:03.540 --> 00:02:07.260 align:middle line:84%
to cantilever and pull the
bone fragments off the cord

00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:09.870 align:middle line:84%
and open up room
for a spinal cord

00:02:09.870 --> 00:02:13.380 align:middle line:90%
to flow up and down to the body.

00:02:13.380 --> 00:02:17.520 align:middle line:84%
And I think if it was
anybody else that I

00:02:17.520 --> 00:02:20.490 align:middle line:84%
had seen an X-ray for
or a CAT scan or an MRI,

00:02:20.490 --> 00:02:23.410 align:middle line:84%
I probably would've recommended
the Harrington rod surgery.

00:02:23.410 --> 00:02:25.680 align:middle line:90%
But this was me.

00:02:25.680 --> 00:02:30.090 align:middle line:84%
And I wasn't so quick
to make that decision,

00:02:30.090 --> 00:02:31.920 align:middle line:84%
because I thought that
I would be spending

00:02:31.920 --> 00:02:35.520 align:middle line:84%
the rest of my life in pain
or at least on medications

00:02:35.520 --> 00:02:39.210 align:middle line:90%
or partially handicapped.

00:02:39.210 --> 00:02:43.340 align:middle line:84%
And so I decided
against the surgery.

00:02:43.340 --> 00:02:47.030 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, when you go
against convention like that,

00:02:47.030 --> 00:02:50.510 align:middle line:84%
you're always considered
foolhardy and insane.

00:02:50.510 --> 00:02:57.350 align:middle line:84%
But I was willing to weigh
what I knew as in my studies

00:02:57.350 --> 00:02:58.990 align:middle line:90%
against what I didn't know.

00:02:58.990 --> 00:03:01.310 align:middle line:84%
And I was willing
to take a chance

00:03:01.310 --> 00:03:04.250 align:middle line:84%
and see if I could heal
myself without having

00:03:04.250 --> 00:03:06.230 align:middle line:90%
any surgical intervention.

00:03:06.230 --> 00:03:08.450 align:middle line:84%
Of course, they thought I
had post-traumatic stress

00:03:08.450 --> 00:03:09.250 align:middle line:90%
disorder--

00:03:09.250 --> 00:03:11.900 align:middle line:84%
I hit my head-- and that
I was not making any sense

00:03:11.900 --> 00:03:14.630 align:middle line:90%
or I wasn't being reasonable.

00:03:14.630 --> 00:03:18.030 align:middle line:84%
But I just had this thought, you
know, I'm not going anywhere.

00:03:18.030 --> 00:03:19.050 align:middle line:90%
I'm not doing anything.

00:03:19.050 --> 00:03:21.050 align:middle line:90%
I'm laying face down.

00:03:21.050 --> 00:03:23.840 align:middle line:84%
I had some neurological
problems, of course.

00:03:23.840 --> 00:03:26.300 align:middle line:84%
And I just thought, you
know, the power that

00:03:26.300 --> 00:03:27.890 align:middle line:90%
made the body heals the body.

00:03:27.890 --> 00:03:31.760 align:middle line:84%
And this vitalistic
intelligence that's

00:03:31.760 --> 00:03:35.120 align:middle line:84%
giving us life on a
moment-to-moment basis

00:03:35.120 --> 00:03:36.020 align:middle line:90%
is a consciousness.

00:03:36.020 --> 00:03:37.460 align:middle line:84%
And consciousness
is an awareness.

00:03:37.460 --> 00:03:38.877 align:middle line:84%
And awareness is
paying attention.

00:03:38.877 --> 00:03:40.640 align:middle line:90%
It's an intelligence.

00:03:40.640 --> 00:03:42.080 align:middle line:90%
And it has an amazing will.

00:03:42.080 --> 00:03:43.790 align:middle line:90%
It has an unlimited mind.

00:03:43.790 --> 00:03:45.530 align:middle line:90%
And it's loving us in the life.

00:03:45.530 --> 00:03:48.920 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, well, if my
will could match its will,

00:03:48.920 --> 00:03:52.700 align:middle line:84%
if my mind could match its
mind, and my love for life

00:03:52.700 --> 00:03:55.460 align:middle line:84%
could match its
love for life, maybe

00:03:55.460 --> 00:03:58.160 align:middle line:84%
I could make contact
with it, give it a plan,

00:03:58.160 --> 00:04:00.530 align:middle line:84%
give it a template,
give it a design.

00:04:00.530 --> 00:04:03.957 align:middle line:84%
And when I was happy
with that design,

00:04:03.957 --> 00:04:05.540 align:middle line:84%
I knew that I couldn't
do the healing.

00:04:05.540 --> 00:04:08.800 align:middle line:84%
So I would surrender my
creation to a greater mind

00:04:08.800 --> 00:04:13.380 align:middle line:84%
and just see what the autonomic
nervous system could do.

00:04:13.380 --> 00:04:16.640 align:middle line:90%
So it sounds really easy.

00:04:16.640 --> 00:04:20.480 align:middle line:84%
But I think that when
we're in crisis or trauma,

00:04:20.480 --> 00:04:23.630 align:middle line:84%
we tend to focus on what we
don't want to have happen

00:04:23.630 --> 00:04:26.010 align:middle line:84%
instead of what we do
want to have happen.

00:04:26.010 --> 00:04:28.460 align:middle line:84%
So I made a deal with
myself that I was going

00:04:28.460 --> 00:04:31.140 align:middle line:90%
to reconstruct my entire spine.

00:04:31.140 --> 00:04:33.620 align:middle line:84%
And I wasn't going to let any
thought slip by my awareness

00:04:33.620 --> 00:04:36.580 align:middle line:84%
that I didn't want
to experience.

00:04:36.580 --> 00:04:40.330 align:middle line:84%
And so I went through about six
or seven weeks of total hell

00:04:40.330 --> 00:04:44.350 align:middle line:84%
because I couldn't get my mind
to do what I wanted it to do.

00:04:44.350 --> 00:04:46.900 align:middle line:84%
I'd start off reconstructing
the vertebrae in my spine.

00:04:46.900 --> 00:04:47.800 align:middle line:84%
And then the next
thing you know,

00:04:47.800 --> 00:04:49.800 align:middle line:84%
I'd be thinking about
living the rest of my life

00:04:49.800 --> 00:04:51.427 align:middle line:90%
in a wheelchair.

00:04:51.427 --> 00:04:53.260 align:middle line:84%
And I'd become conscious
that I was focusing

00:04:53.260 --> 00:04:54.820 align:middle line:84%
on what I didn't
want to have happen

00:04:54.820 --> 00:04:56.920 align:middle line:84%
instead of what I did
want to have happen.

00:04:56.920 --> 00:04:58.930 align:middle line:84%
Then I'd start from the
very beginning again.

00:04:58.930 --> 00:05:00.742 align:middle line:90%
And I reconstruct my spine.

00:05:00.742 --> 00:05:02.950 align:middle line:84%
And then I'd be thinking
about should I sell my home?

00:05:02.950 --> 00:05:04.180 align:middle line:90%
Should I sell my practice?

00:05:04.180 --> 00:05:05.830 align:middle line:84%
And all the people
in my life were

00:05:05.830 --> 00:05:07.340 align:middle line:90%
telling me to sell everything.

00:05:07.340 --> 00:05:11.710 align:middle line:84%
But if I accepted the
belief on some level

00:05:11.710 --> 00:05:14.290 align:middle line:84%
that I would be
able to walk again,

00:05:14.290 --> 00:05:17.350 align:middle line:84%
I should never sell my
home and sell my practice.

00:05:17.350 --> 00:05:20.050 align:middle line:84%
And so no one could
relate with me.

00:05:20.050 --> 00:05:22.930 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's the beginning
of the dark night of the soul

00:05:22.930 --> 00:05:25.180 align:middle line:90%
when nobody gets you but you.

00:05:25.180 --> 00:05:26.920 align:middle line:84%
And you're crossing
a river of change,

00:05:26.920 --> 00:05:27.970 align:middle line:84%
and you're weighing
what you know

00:05:27.970 --> 00:05:29.137 align:middle line:90%
against what you don't know.

00:05:29.137 --> 00:05:32.110 align:middle line:84%
And you realize nobody
has the answers but you.

00:05:32.110 --> 00:05:37.870 align:middle line:84%
So in those six weeks, it
would take me 2 and 1/2

00:05:37.870 --> 00:05:39.730 align:middle line:90%
hours to reconstruct my spine.

00:05:39.730 --> 00:05:43.980 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of
about six weeks,

00:05:43.980 --> 00:05:47.710 align:middle line:84%
beginning of the seventh week, I
went through the entire process

00:05:47.710 --> 00:05:49.540 align:middle line:90%
without losing my focus.

00:05:49.540 --> 00:05:51.940 align:middle line:84%
And it was like hitting a
tennis ball in the sweet spot.

00:05:51.940 --> 00:05:54.340 align:middle line:90%
Something clicked for me.

00:05:54.340 --> 00:05:56.620 align:middle line:84%
And from that point on,
everything got easier.

00:05:56.620 --> 00:05:59.380 align:middle line:84%
I was able to do what I
was doing in 2 and 1/2

00:05:59.380 --> 00:06:01.840 align:middle line:90%
hours in 45 minutes.

00:06:01.840 --> 00:06:03.940 align:middle line:84%
Little did I know that
I was firing and wiring

00:06:03.940 --> 00:06:06.220 align:middle line:84%
circuits in my brain
and at the same time,

00:06:06.220 --> 00:06:10.720 align:middle line:84%
I was increasing my ability to
pay attention and stay present.

00:06:10.720 --> 00:06:14.860 align:middle line:84%
And so when I started
noticing those strong changes

00:06:14.860 --> 00:06:15.700 align:middle line:90%
in my body--

00:06:15.700 --> 00:06:16.540 align:middle line:90%
the numbness went away.

00:06:16.540 --> 00:06:17.340 align:middle line:90%
The pain went away.

00:06:17.340 --> 00:06:20.530 align:middle line:84%
I started having
more motor function--

00:06:20.530 --> 00:06:23.020 align:middle line:84%
I started to correlate what
I was doing inside of me

00:06:23.020 --> 00:06:26.080 align:middle line:84%
with the effects I was
producing outside of me.

00:06:26.080 --> 00:06:29.920 align:middle line:84%
And the moment I was able to
correlate that connection,

00:06:29.920 --> 00:06:33.010 align:middle line:84%
I did it with more passion,
more sincerity, more enthusiasm,

00:06:33.010 --> 00:06:35.650 align:middle line:84%
instead of dreading going
through the process.

00:06:35.650 --> 00:06:39.910 align:middle line:84%
And that was the switch for me,
because from that moment on,

00:06:39.910 --> 00:06:43.360 align:middle line:84%
my body started to respond
to my mind very quickly.

00:06:43.360 --> 00:06:47.650 align:middle line:84%
And they told me that I'd
probably never walk again.

00:06:47.650 --> 00:06:51.070 align:middle line:84%
They told me that I
would have to live

00:06:51.070 --> 00:06:54.220 align:middle line:90%
in a body cast for a year.

00:06:54.220 --> 00:06:57.110 align:middle line:84%
And that I'd be
handicapped in some way.

00:06:57.110 --> 00:07:03.640 align:middle line:84%
And was back on my feet in
a little less than 10 weeks.

00:07:03.640 --> 00:07:06.520 align:middle line:90%
I was back training at 12 weeks.

00:07:06.520 --> 00:07:09.820 align:middle line:84%
And to this day I really
have no pain in my spine.

00:07:09.820 --> 00:07:11.680 align:middle line:84%
And I just made a
deal with myself.

00:07:11.680 --> 00:07:14.680 align:middle line:84%
In those lonely
nights, you know,

00:07:14.680 --> 00:07:17.140 align:middle line:84%
I thought if I'm ever
able to walk again,

00:07:17.140 --> 00:07:19.750 align:middle line:84%
I promised myself
that I'll spend

00:07:19.750 --> 00:07:22.720 align:middle line:84%
the rest of my life studying
the mind-body connection

00:07:22.720 --> 00:07:23.890 align:middle line:90%
and mind over matter.

00:07:23.890 --> 00:07:25.900 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I've
been doing since 1986.

